# Assignment 3 – To-Do List Application

## Course
COMP1073 – Client-Side JavaScript  
## Group Details
**Group Number:** Group 3

### Members:
- Hiyaben Hareshbhai Jayswal
- Abiskar Chhetri


## Description

This project is a web-based To-Do List application built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

The application allows users to:
- Add tasks
- Mark tasks as complete
- Delete tasks
- Interact with a dynamic and user-friendly interface


## Work Distribution
### Hiyaben Hareshbhai Jayswal (JavaScript)
- Implemented:
  - Add task
  - Delete task
  - Checkbox functionality
  - Move completed tasks to bottom
  - Task counter
- Added:
  - Ding sound on completion
  - Delete sound
  - Pre-filled demo tasks
  - Enter key support
- Handled all JavaScript logic and DOM manipulation

### Abiskar Chhetri (Frontend & Design)
- Created HTML structure (index.html)
- Designed CSS styling (style.css)
- Implemented:
  - Layout and spacing
  - Button styling and hover effects
  - Task list UI design
  - Animations (fade, hover glow)
- Added:
  - Checklist image
  - “Task added!” message UI
  - Responsive design


## Features
### Core Features
- Add tasks dynamically
- Each task includes:
  - Checkbox
  - Task text
  - Delete button
- Mark tasks complete (line-through effect)
- Move completed tasks to bottom
- Delete tasks

### Additional Features
- Sound effects (ding + delete)
- Smooth animations (fade, hover effects)
- “Task added!” pop-up message
- Task counter
- Enter key support
- Pre-filled demo tasks
- Checklist image


## 🛠️ Technologies Used
- HTML5
- CSS3 (Flexbox, transitions, animations)
- JavaScript (DOM manipulation, events, arrays)

## 🎯 Conclusion

This To-Do List application demonstrates strong understanding of client-side JavaScript, DOM manipulation, and UI design while meeting all technical and creative requirements.
